I want to talk about POSTIVE SELF TALK for ONE HOT MINUTE!! Michael Johnson just snapped this picture during our PiYo workout.  I was excited because I was feeling pretty STRONG and CONFIDENT in this half moon pose.

BUT when I looked at the picture suddenly words started coming out of my mouth like.. FAT
CHUBBY
THICK
BIG BELLY

Thank goodness for my sweet husband for reminding me that I am not FAT, CHUBBY, THICK, or have a BIG BELLY.  That what you see in this picture is GRAVITY and it happens after you grow two babies.  I am STRONG, CONFIDENT, and HEALTHY.

Do you know which words made me FEEL BETTER?? The POSTIVE ONES. 
Do you know which ones are THE TRUTH?? The POSTIVE ONES.

When you look at pictures of yourself, what kind of words do you use to describe yourself?? Are they words that you would use to describe your children?? If you wouldn't call someone else those things, why IN THE WORLD would you say them to yourself.

This is your reminder that IT'S OKAY to not be perfect but IT IS NOT OKAY to be MEAN to yourself!! Your body hears everything your mind says... BE POSTIVE!!
